Phone	Retailer/Manufacturer
customer support, product completeness
Contacting the retailer or manufacturer is necessary if any phone accessories are missing from the unboxing.

Phone	User Manual/Warranty Card
documentation, setup guidance
The User Manual and Warranty Card provide essential information for setting up and understanding warranty coverage of the phone.

Phone	Screen Protector
protection, device care
A Screen Protector is applied to enhance the durability and resistance against scratches on the phoneâ€™s screen.

MicroSD Card	Phone
storage expansion, compatibility
The MicroSD Card expands the storage capacity of a smartphone if it supports expandable storage.

Phone	eSIM Technology
modern connectivity, wireless management
eSIM technology allows users to manage their SIM card information digitally on compatible phones without physical cards.

Phone	Wi-Fi Network
connectivity, cost-saving
Connecting to a Wi-Fi network enables internet access for the phone without using cellular data.

Google Account/Apple ID	Phone
access, personalization
Signing into a Google Account or Apple ID unlocks various features and services on Android or iOS devices respectively.

Find My Device	Google Account
security, device recovery
The Find My Device feature is available through signing in with a Google Account, enabling phone tracking for security purposes.

Google Drive/iCloud	Phone
data protection, cloud storage
Google Drive and iCloud are used to backup data from phones, ensuring data safety and ease of access across devices.

Google Play Store/App Store	Phone
app access, digital marketplace
The Google Play Store and App Store provide a platform for downloading applications on Android and iOS devices respectively.

Bloatware	Phone
system optimization, user preference
Bloatware refers to pre-installed apps that users may find unnecessary; these can be disabled or uninstalled to optimize phone performance.

Mobile Data	SIM card
activation, connectivity
The SIM card is crucial for enabling mobile data usage on the phone.

Front Camera	Rear Camera
camera check, setup process
Both cameras are tested during setup to ensure comprehensive photographic functionality of the device.

Microphone	Speakers
audio test, functionality verification
The speakers and microphone are paired functionalities for audio output and input, both tested together during phone setup.

Biometric Security	Find My Device
security features, loss prevention
Biometric security enhances personal device protection, which complements the Find My Device feature in case of loss or theft.

Automatic Backups	privacy and security settings
data protection, configuration step
Enabling automatic backups is part of configuring privacy and security settings to safeguard data.

Brightness Settings	Dark Mode
personalization, user experience
Both brightness settings and dark mode are personalization features aimed at improving user experience by adjusting visual display preferences.

Notification Sounds	Widgets
customization, setup process
Customizing notification sounds is part of setting up widgets and other elements for a personalized phone interface.

Frequently Used Apps	Home Screen
organization, usability enhancement
Organizing frequently used apps on the home screen enhances accessibility and efficiency in navigation.
